OBX|2|FT|24531-6^CT Abdomen^LN|2|FINDINGS: CT of the abdomen and pelvis was done following oral and during\.br\intravenous contrast infusion.\.br\\.br\There are a few scattered diverticula in the colon but no findings\.br\that suggest acute diverticulitis.  The gallbladder and bile ducts\.br\appear normal.\.br\\.br\There is a 1.2 cm spherical cortical mass in the right mid kidney\.br\posteriorly.  This measures between 100 and 130 Hounsfield units\.br\and therefore appears to be a solid mass although it may be a\.br\hyperdense cyst.  Further evaluation is recommended.  Consider\.br\ultrasound and CT following day renal mass protocol for further\.br\assessment.  There are no findings that suggest acute aisle\.br\arthritis.\.br\\.br\No evidence of bowel obstruction or splenic pathology.  No\.br\findings to suggest pancreatitis.||||||F
