OBR|10||ACC-P2-0010|24690-0^US Retroperitoneal Complete^LN|||20070825103100||||||Followup for right renal lesion.||||||||||||F
OBX|1|TX|24690-0^US Retroperitoneal Complete^LN|1|CLINICAL INDICATION: Followup for right renal lesion.||||||F
OBX|2|FT|24690-0^US Retroperitoneal Complete^LN|2|FINDINGS: Compared to prior CT of 06/16/07.\.br\\.br\The right kidney measures 10.7 cm in length.  There is a 1.8 x 1.1\.br\x 1.3 cm hypoechoic lesion in the interpolar region of the right\.br\kidney corresponding to the lesion seen on CT.  This appears to\.br\have some internal echogenicity, though there is questionable\.br\through transmission on several images.  This may represent a\.br\hemorrhagic cyst.  It is difficult to entirely exclude a complex\.br\cyst given the appearance.  No other renal lesions are seen.\.br\\.br\The left kidney measures 10.6 cm in length and appears normal in\.br\echo texture.\.br\\.br\The bladder appears normal.\.br\\.br\\.br\\.br\** IMPRESSION **:\.br\Hypoechoic right renal lesion, as described.  This corresponds to\.br\the lesion seen on CT.  Given the ultrasound appearance, it is\.br\still nonspecific, though suggestive of a cyst.  It could be a\.br\resolving hemorrhagic cyst or cyst with internal debris.  Given\.br\the appearance, consider continued surveillance by ultrasound.  A\.br\follow-up exam could be performed in approximately 3-6 months to\.br\assure stability.||||||F
ZDS|1.2.840.113619.2.55.3.2.10^NEWVUE_PACS^Application^DICOM
