OBX|3|FT|36643-5^XR Chest^LN|3|FINDINGS: Lines/tubes:  None.\.br\Cardiac, mediastinal, and hilar contours:  Cardiomediastinal\.br\silhouette and pulmonary vascularity are within normal limits.\.br\Calcified plaque involves the thoracic aorta.\.br\Lungs:  Linear bibasilar opacities are most suggestive of\.br\atelectasis although superimposed consolidation cannot be\.br\excluded. No appreciable pleural effusion or pneumothorax\.br\detected.\.br\Bones:  Grossly unremarkable.\.br\Soft tissues:  Unremarkable.\.br\ \.br\** IMPRESSION **:\.br\Linear bibasilar opacities are most suggestive of atelectasis\.br\although superimposed consolidation cannot be excluded.\.br\ \.br\Aortic atherosclerosis.||||||F
