OBR|14||ACC-P2-0014|24532-4^CT Abdomen and Pelvis^LN|||20120929115100||||||68-year-old male status post prostatectomy here for abdominal pain and right flank pain. Rule out abscess.||||||||||||F
OBX|1|TX|24532-4^CT Abdomen and Pelvis^LN|1|CLINICAL INDICATION: 68-year-old male status post prostatectomy here for abdominal pain and right flank pain. Rule out abscess.||||||F
OBX|2|FT|24532-4^CT Abdomen and Pelvis^LN|2|FINDINGS: Technique: Axial images of the abdomen and pelvis were obtained\.br\with IV administration of 148 mL of Omnipaque-300.\.br\ \.br\CTDI: 24.03 mGy\.br\DLP: 1294.02 mGy-cm\.br\ \.br\Comparison is made with 06/16/2007.\.br\ \.br\Dependent atelectasis is seen posteriorly at both lung bases.\.br\ \.br\The liver, spleen, pancreas, adrenals, and gallbladder appear\.br\unremarkable. The left kidney appears normal.\.br\ \.br\Posteriorly in the midpole of the right kidney, a hypodense mass\.br\is seen measuring 1.8 x 1.6 x 2.0 cm. This appears slightly larger\.br\than it did on prior exam. Previously, it measured approximately\.br\1.5 x 1.3 x 1.5 cm. No hydronephrosis or renal calculi are seen.\.br\No ureteral calculi are noted. No inflammatory changes seen\.br\surrounding either kidney. No perinephric fluid collection or\.br\perinephric abscess is present.\.br\ \.br\Scattered diverticuli are seen in the sigmoid colon. There is no\.br\evidence for diverticulitis. The bowel is otherwise unremarkable.\.br\No significant adenopathy is seen within the abdomen or pelvis. No\.br\free fluid or focal fluid collections are noted. A catheter is\.br\seen in the bladder.\.br\ \.br\No suspicious lytic or blastic bony lesions are identified.\.br\ \.br\** IMPRESSION **:\.br\1. Hypodense mass posteriorly in the midpole of the right kidney.\.br\This mass appears to have been present on prior study from 2007\.br\but is slightly increased in size. Prior ultrasound evaluation in\.br\2007 was indeterminate. Again it is unclear whether this\.br\represents a complicated cyst or a solid mass. While the mass has\.br\not increased significantly in size from prior exam, malignancy\.br\cannot entirely be excluded. Further evaluation with renal\.br\protocol CT or MRI may be helpful to further evaluate the lesion.\.br\ \.br\2. No inflammatory change, fluid collection, or evidence for\.br\abscess.\.br\3. Dependent atelectasis at both lung bases.||||||F
