OBX|4|FT|30578-9^CTA Head and Neck^LN|4|FINDINGS: CTA HEAD: Calcified atherosclerotic plaques in the bilateral cavernous ICAs with mild stenosis. Distal flow is maintained. No occlusion. No aneurysm.\.br\ \.br\CTA NECK\.br\GREAT VESSELS: Visualized segments are patent. Aortic atherosclerosis.\.br\ \.br\RIGHT ICA: No stenosis or significant plaque.  No dissection.\.br\ \.br\LEFT ICA: No stenosis or occlusion. Mild calcified plaque.  No dissection.\.br\ \.br\VERTEBRAL ARTERIES: Patent extracranial segments.  No dissection.\.br\ \.br\OTHER: Suggestion of 1.3 cm left thyroid gland nodule. The right thyroid gland is small. Small calcified granuloma in the right upper lobe. Degenerative changes of the cervical spine. Chronic complete opacification of the right sphenoid sinus.||||||F
