OBX|4|FT|24627-2^CT Chest^LN|4|FINDINGS: HEART: Heart size normal.  \.br\VESSELS: Coronary and aortic calcification.\.br\LYMPH NODES: No suspicious lymph nodes. Small mediastinal and hilar calcified lymph nodes compatible with remote granulomatous disease.\.br\OTHER MEDIASTINUM: No significant abnormality.\.br\LUNGS: Small bilateral calcified granulomas. No suspicious pulmonary nodule. Atelectatic changes are present at the lung bases.\.br\PLEURAL SPACE: Normal.\.br\UPPER ABDOMEN: Please see abdominal and pelvic CT results performed concurrently.\.br\SOFT TISSUES: No significant abnormality.\.br\BONES: No suspicious lytic or blastic lesions. Degenerative changes of the spine. Mild anterior T12 vertebral body compression fracture, appearing likely chronic. There is also an age-indeterminate L1 vertebral body compression fracture, better characterized on dedicated abdomen and pelvis CT reported separately.\.br\\.br\\.br\\.br\\.br\STUDIES COPIED TO HERE:||||||F
