OBX|4|FT|24725-4^CT Head^LN|4|FINDINGS: BRAIN PARENCHYMA/VENTRICLES/EXTRA-AXIAL SPACES: There is no acute intraparenchymal hemorrhage. There is diffuse central and cortical volume loss. Stable old lacunar infarct in the right internal capsule.\.br\ \.br\There is mixed density subdural hematoma along the left frontoparietal convexity which is predominantly hypodense with subtle intrinsic isodensity. No acute component. It measures about 9 mm in maximum transverse width (previously uniformly hypodense measuring about 5 mm in maximum transverse width). No significant mass effect or hydrocephalus. No midline shift..\.br\ \.br\EXTRACRANIAL STRUCTURES: Normal bones and soft tissues. Mastoid air cells are clear. Similar complete opacification of right sphenoid sinus with mucoperiosteal thickening consistent with chronic sinusitis.||||||F
